<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9695673157584></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9695673157584><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=9695673157584>RE: What's all this LVL-LVL REAL FAST??</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=9695673157584#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=1226><span id= >Rakluz</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>41 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Sep 21st 4:15 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.22]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>if your saying you love 5 gold, then your not very high level yet.  Let me tell you, im lvl 22 and it takes way more then 50 kills, and different mobs DO give different amounts of exp.<br><br>Example: When I solo a lvl 25 bard NPC, I get less experience then when I kill a lvl 25 treant grouped with people that are even to red (most are higher then me).  Techinichally, I should get less form the treat because the people are higher level and i am splitting the exp, however, treants are widely known for their great exp.<br><br>Another factor is spawn time.  Obviously a mob that takes 5 minutes to respawn will yield more exp then a mob that takes 15 minutes.<br><br>Loot is a different category, and seems to be independant from exp.  While treants are great exp, their loot really bites.  Aviak guards in Lake Rathe are good exp to solo because they give a fair amount of exp, can be soloed, and have a puny 5 minute spawn time.  Again, the loot isnt that great.  <br><br>Loot vs. exp- example- Fighting lizard defenders in cazic thule or the hermit in south karana can give you fine steel weapons, which is GREAT for my level, but the defenders are probably about average exp, and the hermit happens to be quite good exp (which is why hes always camped).  Both give great loot, yet the exp difference is noticeable.<br><br>I feel I have done a fairly good job explaining it, if anyone wants to mention something I may have forgot then please do.<br>&nbsp;<br>Rakluz Roksmasha - ubertroll - 35 Troll SK - &lt;The Storm's Eye&gt;<br>-=Nameless Server=-</td></tr>
