<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96826699816758></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96826699816758><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=96826699816758>RE: Mana v. Int Gear</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=96826699816758#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=347><span id= >Kithias</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>12 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Sep 6th 3:03 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just to clarify:<br><br>Platinum Jade Rings give +20 HP/Mana.<br>Platinum Star Rose Rings gives +4 Int.<br><br>So, when would you want to switch them out? Well, here is the basic formula for figuring out how much mana you get for things that boost your mana AFTER your base racial Int.<br><br>Lets use your example. You have two rings that give you +40 mana total, or, you have two rings that give you +8 Int. Using the known mana calculators on EQ sites, wearing the Int rings will give you 8 x level / 5 = bonus mana.<br><br>So at level 10, you'll get 16 bonus mana from those rings (8 x 10 is 80 / 5 is 16), at level 15 youll get 24, and at 20 youll get 32. But it isnt until 25th level that you truly hit the best Int/mana balance for items. At 25th level, you will be getting 40 mana for those two +4 Int rings...and 40 split between each hand is 20 mana from each ring, just as good as Platinum Jade rings. Of course, you get the +20 HP with the others, but at level 30 when you start to get 48 mana for them and at level 40 when you start to get 64 mana, +Int items beat +mana items every time.<br><br>That is, of course, if you havent reached the cap on Int at 200. Once you hit 200, Int doesnt return as much mana per point, so mana items are the way to go.<br><br>Hope this helps and I didnt give too long an answer. ;)<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Happy Hunting,<br>Kith</td></tr>
