<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96873467429347></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96873467429347><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=96873467429347>RE: Suggestions For Group Play</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=96873467429347#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=865><span id=Sage>Ezzlan</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>38 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Sep 12th 12:57 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.80]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Necromancers fill many roles in a group.<br><br>The Necromancer brings to the group power, pure unbridled, power, we allow small groups to excel<br><br>1. The Necromancer is a mana battery at the least, Their mana regen spells allow us to gain mana and give (ack) or use more spells than anyone else. As per my iksar Necromancer guide (posted on the iksar page I believe, I'll repost here if someone asks for it) a necromancers life is learning that mana = health health = mana, they are interchangable, and not just within yourself, but we have the power to take the enemies health and make it into our health, and through that make it into our mana.  (a tad confusing, but its true).<br><br>2. Perhaps most importantly we are warriors, our pets are almost as strong as a magicians, and assist small groups through doing tons of damage, and being able to absorb a small amount as well. However, you will still need a tank in your group.<br><br>3. We are wizards, not in the sense of doing DD or evacs (unless you count our undead only dds), but in an emergency situation a necro can save the groups life, fear can and will save a group member from an aggroed mob.<br><br>4. We are quasi Healers, WE take HPs from the target, spending mana, We turn those HPs into the HPs of our fellow players. Not efficient in this capacity, however, it is still possible to save someones life in an emergency situation.<br><br>5. We are also Quasi Enchanters, we have the ability to mez a target, Its not a good spell, but its better than nothing, and if you lack an enchanter, its better than dieing.<br><br>Ok, so now that I have explained who we are as necromancers, perhaps you see where we fit into groups, We are the ultimate "magic attack" class, we will do almost as much damage in the group as a warrior, while at the same time, being able to reduce downtime, our pets heal a heck of a lot faster than a warrior ;) plus if the pet dies you can always resummon while the tank taunts off you.<br><br>So there you have it, We should be just as valued additions to a group as a wizard or mage, if not more.<br><br>If you want to "wow" the group with your tactics, learn how to pull, its easy to do in the early levels, and with the pet guard here command in certain zones can be great, You cast a spell such as a dot you were going to cast anyways, and the tank saves their mana or arrows for when they are more needed.  <br><br>As for skills, communication is vital, as with any other class of course, and this is where many necromancers are sorely lacking unfortunatly, Soloing will not get you into higher leveled places into the game.  When you are level 20 and in a group of 3 or 4 taking down whites and yellows NON-STOP This is when people will bow before you as a god, you are unstopable, they will whine of being LOM and your pet will say bring em on. <br>If someone is down to 3 bubbles and you are FH heal em, reducing downtime is god in this game ;)<br><br>Ok if I didn't say it enough, the necromancer brings offensive power to a group, they make a fine addition when you are looking for a secondary tank, try a necromancer instead, you will be greatly surprised if the necro is worth is weight in salt, and if the necro is grouping he probly is ;) Not only do we do damage, we have a few nice touches thrown in for flavor.<br><br>When I say these things though, do not take it that I do not value the other classes, I simply adore them, Do not try to step on the toes of the other classes you group with, don't try to burn mana like the wizard, don't try to mez like an enchanter, instead compliment their skills, if fighting a tougher mob, perhaps lay on the dots which will give more reliable damage, and then let the wizards burn the yellows - blues. Definatly don't step on an enchanters feet while grouping with him, know exactly on whats mobs and when to lay your dot(s), why not leave the main mezzing up to him, and instead offer to grab anything that goes after him, act as his guardian angel. hey if not mez, you could root something that goes after the enchanter or cleric, giving them desperate time to get away or mez the target, you save their lives and you will earn the respect.<br><br>*edited a bit shortly after I originally wrote it to include the final blurb*<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Ezzlan 25th ENC Brell<br>Antarius 35th Bard Terris-Thule</td></tr>
